RT @truethevoteIf you aren’t familiar with ERIC, this is the Electronic Registration Information Center.

https://ericstates.org/

What info can ERIC get about you? Your voter file, your drivers license file, citizenship docs, and info from any health/human service agency.

Here’s a link to the Illinois ERIC contract.

https://www.dropbox.com/s/8uujlni90e3lkqd/ERIC%20Agreement.pdf?dl=0

1. Why do they need ALL this info?
2. With all of this, why are voter rolls still inaccurate?

ERIC is not what it seems.

RT @truethevote If you live in one of the 32 states (+ DC) in “membership” with ERIC you have a right to know what data is being released about you.

Our attnys have checked off on a open records template we can all send to get our personal “ERIC file”.

One of the requirements of ERIC’s contract is that info NOT be released. That’s unconstitutional … so this will be interesting.

We’ll post the letter on our website. If you can join us Mon 8/29 @ 7p to discuss, I’ll be here

https://truethevote.locals.com/
